>Can I hook up an Ammeter gauge....to see if my alternator is working to
capacity...from existing wiring and senders in my '74 1.8L westy?  Wiring
diagrams in Bentley, for me, are like....trigonometry..or a paper chase!
Cheers.
>Syd

I wired in a volt meter connected at the front of the vehicle. The ammeter may
show you the amount being produced by the alternator but the voltmeter
connected at the front shows you what is actually getting through to the front
where almost every important piece of wiring passes through!

Martin.
